Foot & mouth disease - Mongolia: OIE confirmation 20010225.0368
Foot & mouth disease, cattle - Mongolia 20010222.0345
Foot & mouth disease, suspected - Mongolia 20010214.0294
[1
Date: 5 Mar 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, 5 Mar 2001 [edited

Mongolian authorities are battling to contain Foot-and-Mouth Disease (FMD),
which is spinning out of control in the eastern part of the country. The
disease has spread to 11 counties of the Dornod, Suhbaator, and Hentiy
provinces in the east
The central government has decided to expand isolation areas and more
animals would receive vaccination. Meanwhile, the Ulan Bator municipality
has ordered extra measures to fend off the epidemic from the capital.
In Dornod and Suhbaator, some 1.6 million animals had been checked, 300 000
of them vaccinated. In the worst affected areas, some 60 000 livestock were
found infected and are being slaughtered. The government is isolating farms
in Kentiy province after new cases of FMD were reported at the end of last
month.
The spread of FMD is another heavy blow to herders of the landlocked
country. Heavy snowstorms have killed more than 1.4 million head of cattle
so far this year.
--
