[2
Date: 5 Mar 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, 2 Mar 2001 [edited

Vaccination is Underway in Mongolia to Contain Foot and Mouth Epidemic
--------------------------------------------
An intensive vaccination is underway in the quarantined area affected by
FMD in the eastern provinces in Mongolia, said an official of the State
Emergency Commission of Mongolia on Friday.
According to the official, the first batch of the vaccine imported from
Russia was being distributed to vaccinate 1.4 million livestock, and a
total of 3.4 million ampoules of vaccine will be imported to stop the
disease from spreading.
The Mongolian government declared a quarantine on 10 Feb 2001 in Sukhbaatar
and Dornod provinces in the east of Mongolia, in which more than a hundred
cows have died of the extremely contagious disease and more than 800 tested
positive.
Some newspapers here Friday reported FMD has spread to the Hentii province,
which is near Ulan Bator, the capital of Mongolial. The Mongolian
government has declared a quarantine in some counties of Hentii province.
