[3
Date: 5 Mar 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ITAR/TASS News Agency, 2 Mar 2001 [edited

Cattle in the Chelyabinsk region of Western Siberia have been under threat
of being infected with FMD as a result of migration of wild animals from
Mongolia.
Eduard Popov, a duty officer of the Krasnoyarsk regional headquarters for
emergency situations, told Itar-Tass that approximately 3000 rams have
crossed into the Russian territory in search of food [that is scarce in
Mongolia, where incidents of FMD were reported. Although no cases of the
cattle epidemic have been diagnosed in the Chita region yet, an emergency
regime was introduced there.
A ban has been imposed on imports of all kinds of cattle from Mongolia and
exports of all kinds of meat and dairy products from the Chita region.
